subSubSection.paragraph:
Taking into consideration the characters studied by Schaefer (
1977
; 
1998
) in his analysis of Hypoptopomatinae, the following anatomical features are present in 

P. bahiensis

: 
1
) nasal capsule opened; 
2
) compound pterotic pierced by numerous enlarged fenestrae; 
3
) metapterygoid channel present; 
4
) partially closed arrector fossae of the ventral pectoral girdle; 
5
) presence of a large median rostral plate; 
6
) snout region odontodes enlarged; 
7
) metapterigoid with deep channel; 
8
) preopercle ventral margin reflected medially; 
9
) rostral plate with posterior notch articulation to the mesethmoid; 
10
) fourth infraorbital expanded ventrally.
